# BwnX Platform Cursor AI Rules

## Project Overview
BwnX Platform is a recommendation system for life, money, and lifestyle using AI and deep personalization.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Supabase Database
- Clerk Authentication
- OpenAI API
- Upstash Redis
- PostHog Analytics

## Code Style Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Follow ESLint rules
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling
- Use React Server Components where possible
- Use client components only when necessary
- Follow the folder structure:
  - `/app` - Next.js App Router pages
  - `/components` - UI components
  - `/lib` - Utility functions and services
  - `/types` - TypeScript types
  - `/public` - Static assets

## Debugging Tips
- Check Supabase connection in lib/supabase.ts
- Verify Clerk authentication in app/layout.tsx
- Check OpenAI API integration in lib/ai.ts
- Verify Redis connection in lib/redis.ts

## Common Issues
- Clerk authentication requires proper environment variables
- Supabase requires proper environment variables
- OpenAI API requires valid API key
- Tailwind classes might need purging for production

